FIREWALL: outbound request blocked by the container allowlist.

This is NOT a DNS, connectivity, or bad-URL problem. This container has no
direct route to the internet -- all outbound traffic goes through a Squid
forward proxy that enforces a default-deny allowlist, and the requested host
is not on it.

  Blocked: %u

To allow this destination, add its domain to the firewall allowlist FROM THE
HOST (a process inside the container cannot change its own allowlist):

  * Control web UI:  http://127.0.0.1:8088
  * On the host:     docker exec <firewall-container> fw allow <domain> [ttl]

Permanent default: add the domain to
.devcontainer/firewall/allowlist.default and rebuild the firewall image.
See README.md -> "Manage the allowlist from the host".
